3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* postcat 1
6/* SUMMARY
7/* show Postfix queue file contents
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* \fBpostcat\fR [\fB-bdehnoqv\fR] [\fB-c \fIconfig_dir\fR] [\fIfiles\fR...]
10/* DESCRIPTION
11/* The \fBpostcat\fR(1) command prints the contents of the
12/* named \fIfiles\fR in human-readable form. The files are
13/* expected to be in Postfix queue file format. If no \fIfiles\fR
14/* are specified on the command line, the program reads from
15/* standard input.
16/*
17/* By default, \fBpostcat\fR(1) shows the envelope and message
18/* content, as if the options \fB-beh\fR were specified. To
19/* view message content only, specify \fB-bh\fR (Postfix 2.7
20/* and later).
21/*
22/* Options:
23/* .IP \fB-b\fR
24/* Show body content. The \fB-b\fR option starts producing
25/* output at the first non-header line, and stops when the end
26/* of the message is reached.
27/* .sp
28/* This feature is available in Postfix 2.7 and later.
29/* .IP "\fB-c \fIconfig_dir\fR"
30/* The \fBmain.cf\fR configuration file is in the named directory
31/* instead of the default configuration directory.
32/* .IP \fB-d\fR
33/* Print the decimal type of each record.
34/* .IP \fB-e\fR
35/* Show message envelope content.
36/* .sp
37/* This feature is available in Postfix 2.7 and later.
38/* .IP \fB-h\fR
39/* Show message header content. The \fB-h\fR option produces
40/* output from the beginning of the message up to, but not
41/* including, the first non-header line.
42/* .sp
43/* This feature is available in Postfix 2.7 and later.
44/* .IP \fB-o\fR
45/* Print the queue file offset of each record.
46/* .IP \fB-q\fR
47/* Search the Postfix queue for the named \fIfiles\fR instead
48/* of taking the names literally.
49/*
50/* This feature is available in Postfix 2.0 and later.
51/* .IP \fB-v\fR
52/* Enable verbose logging for debugging purposes. Multiple \fB-v\fR
53/* options make the software increasingly verbose.
54/* DIAGNOSTICS
55/* Problems are reported to the standard error stream.
56/* ENVIRONMENT
57/* .ad
58/* .fi
59/* .IP \fBMAIL_CONFIG\fR
60/* Directory with Postfix configuration files.
61/* CONFIGURATION PARAMETERS
62/* .ad
63/* .fi
64/* The following \fBmain.cf\fR parameters are especially relevant to
65/* this program.
66/*
67/* The text below provides only a parameter summary. See
68/* \fBpostconf\fR(5) for more details including examples.
69/* .IP "\fBconfig_directory (see 'postconf -d' output)\fR"
70/* The default location of the Postfix main.cf and master.cf
71/* configuration files.
72/* .IP "\fBqueue_directory (see 'postconf -d' output)\fR"
73/* The location of the Postfix top-level queue directory.
74/* FILES
75/* /var/spool/postfix, Postfix queue directory
76/* SEE ALSO
77/* postconf(5), Postfix configuration
78/* LICENSE
79/* .ad
80/* .fi
81/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
82/* AUTHOR(S)
83/* Wietse Venema
84/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
85/* P.O. Box 704
86/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
87/*
88/* Wietse Venema
89/* Google, Inc.
90/* 111 8th Avenue
91/* New York, NY 10011, USA
92/*--*/

128/* Application-specific. */
129
130#define PC_FLAG_SEARCH_QUEUE (1<<0) /* search queue */
131#define PC_FLAG_PRINT_OFFSET (1<<1) /* print record offsets */
132#define PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV (1<<2) /* print envelope records */
133#define PC_FLAG_PRINT_HEADER (1<<3) /* print header records */
134#define PC_FLAG_PRINT_BODY (1<<4) /* print body records */
135#define PC_FLAG_PRINT_RTYPE_DEC (1<<5) /* print decimal record type */
136#define PC_FLAG_PRINT_RTYPE_SYM (1<<6) /* print symbolic record type */
137
138#define PC_MASK_PRINT_TEXT (PC_FLAG_PRINT_HEADER | PC_FLAG_PRINT_BODY)
139#define PC_MASK_PRINT_ALL (PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV | PC_MASK_PRINT_TEXT)
140
141 /*
142 * State machine.
143 */
144#define PC_STATE_ENV 0 /* initial or extracted envelope */
145#define PC_STATE_HEADER 1 /* primary header */
146#define PC_STATE_BODY 2 /* other */
147
148#define STR vstring_str
149#define LEN VSTRING_LEN
150
151/* postcat - visualize Postfix queue file contents */
152
153static void postcat(VSTREAM *fp, VSTRING *buffer, int flags)
154{
155 int prev_type = 0;
156 int rec_type;
157 struct timeval tv;
158 time_t time;
159 int ch;
160 off_t offset;
161 const char *error_text;
162 char *attr_name;
163 char *attr_value;
164 int rec_flags = (msg_verbose ? REC_FLAG_NONE : REC_FLAG_DEFAULT);
165 int state; /* state machine, input type */
166 int do_print; /* state machine, output control */
167 long data_offset; /* state machine, read optimization */
168 long data_size; /* state machine, read optimization */
169
170#define TEXT_RECORD(rec_type) \
171 (rec_type == REC_TYPE_CONT || rec_type == REC_TYPE_NORM)
172
173 /*
174 * See if this is a plausible file.
175 */
176 if ((ch = VSTREAM_GETC(fp)) != VSTREAM_EOF) {
177 if (!strchr(REC_TYPE_ENVELOPE, ch)) {
178 msg_warn("%s: input is not a valid queue file", VSTREAM_PATH(fp));
179 return;
180 }
181 vstream_ungetc(fp, ch);
182 }
183
184 /*
185 * Other preliminaries.
186 */
187 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV)
188 vstream_printf("*** ENVELOPE RECORDS %s ***\n",
189 VSTREAM_PATH(fp));
190 state = PC_STATE_ENV;
191 do_print = (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV);
192 data_offset = data_size = -1;
193
194 /*
195 * Now look at the rest.
196 */
197 for (;;) {
198 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_OFFSET)
199 offset = vstream_ftell(fp);
200 rec_type = rec_get_raw(fp, buffer, 0, rec_flags);
201 if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_ERROR)
202 msg_fatal("record read error");
203 if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_EOF)
204 break;
205
206 /*
207 * First inspect records that have side effects on the (envelope,
208 * header, body) state machine or on the record reading order.
209 *
210 * XXX Comments marked "Optimization:" identify subtle code that will
211 * likely need to be revised when the queue file organization is
212 * changed.
213 */
214#define PRINT_MARKER(flags, fp, offset, type, text) do { \
215 if ((flags) & PC_FLAG_PRINT_OFFSET) \
216 vstream_printf("%9lu ", (unsigned long) (offset)); \
217 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_RTYPE_DEC) \
218 vstream_printf("%3d ", (type)); \
219 vstream_printf("*** %s %s ***\n", (text), VSTREAM_PATH(fp)); \
220 vstream_fflush(VSTREAM_OUT); \
221} while (0)
222
223#define PRINT_RECORD(flags, offset, type, value) do { \
224 if ((flags) & PC_FLAG_PRINT_OFFSET) \
225 vstream_printf("%9lu ", (unsigned long) (offset)); \
226 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_RTYPE_DEC) \
227 vstream_printf("%3d ", (type)); \
228 vstream_printf("%s: %s\n", rec_type_name(rec_type), (value)); \
229 vstream_fflush(VSTREAM_OUT); \
230} while (0)
231
232 if (TEXT_RECORD(rec_type)) {
233 /* This is wrong when the message starts with whitespace. */
234 if (state == PC_STATE_HEADER && (flags & (PC_MASK_PRINT_TEXT))
235 && prev_type != REC_TYPE_CONT && TEXT_RECORD(rec_type)
236 && !(is_header(STR(buffer)) || IS_SPACE_TAB(STR(buffer)[0]))) {
237 /* Update the state machine. */
238 state = PC_STATE_BODY;
239 do_print = (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_BODY);
240 /* Optimization: terminate if nothing left to print. */
241 if (do_print == 0 && (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV) == 0)
242 break;
243 /* Optimization: skip to extracted segment marker. */
244 if (do_print == 0 && (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV)
245 && data_offset >= 0 && data_size >= 0
246 && vstream_fseek(fp, data_offset + data_size, SEEK_SET) < 0)
247 msg_fatal("seek error: %m");
248 }
249 /* Optional output happens further down below. */
250 } else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_MESG) {
251 /* Sanity check. */
252 if (state != PC_STATE_ENV)
253 msg_warn("%s: out-of-order message content marker",
254 VSTREAM_PATH(fp));
255 /* Optional output. */
256 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV)
257 PRINT_MARKER(flags, fp, offset, rec_type, "MESSAGE CONTENTS");
258 /* Optimization: skip to extracted segment marker. */
259 if ((flags & PC_MASK_PRINT_TEXT) == 0
260 && data_offset >= 0 && data_size >= 0
261 && vstream_fseek(fp, data_offset + data_size, SEEK_SET) < 0)
262 msg_fatal("seek error: %m");
263 /* Update the state machine, even when skipping. */
264 state = PC_STATE_HEADER;
265 do_print = (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_HEADER);
266 continue;
267 } else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_XTRA) {
268 /* Sanity check. */
269 if (state != PC_STATE_HEADER && state != PC_STATE_BODY)
270 msg_warn("%s: out-of-order extracted segment marker",
271 VSTREAM_PATH(fp));
272 /* Optional output (terminate preceding header/body line). */
273 if (do_print && prev_type == REC_TYPE_CONT)
274 VSTREAM_PUTCHAR('\n');
275 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV)
276 PRINT_MARKER(flags, fp, offset, rec_type, "HEADER EXTRACTED");
277 /* Update the state machine. */
278 state = PC_STATE_ENV;
279 do_print = (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV);
280 /* Optimization: terminate if nothing left to print. */
281 if (do_print == 0)
282 break;
283 continue;
284 } else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_END) {
285 /* Sanity check. */
286 if (state != PC_STATE_ENV)
287 msg_warn("%s: out-of-order message end marker",
288 VSTREAM_PATH(fp));
289 /* Optional output. */
290 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV)
291 PRINT_MARKER(flags, fp, offset, rec_type, "MESSAGE FILE END");
292 /* Terminate the state machine. */
293 break;
294 } else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_PTR) {
295 /* Optional output. */
296 /* This record type is exposed only with '-v'. */
297 if (do_print)
298 PRINT_RECORD(flags, offset, rec_type, STR(buffer));
299 /* Skip to the pointer's target record. */
300 if (rec_goto(fp, STR(buffer)) == REC_TYPE_ERROR)
301 msg_fatal("bad pointer record, or input is not seekable");
302 continue;
303 } else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_SIZE) {
304 /* Optional output (here before we update the state machine). */
305 if (do_print)
306 PRINT_RECORD(flags, offset, rec_type, STR(buffer));
307 /* Read the message size/offset for the state machine optimizer. */
308 if (data_size >= 0 || data_offset >= 0) {
309 msg_warn("file contains multiple size records");
310 } else {
311 if (sscanf(STR(buffer), "%ld %ld", &data_size, &data_offset) != 2
312 || data_offset <= 0 || data_size <= 0)
313 msg_fatal("invalid size record: %.100s", STR(buffer));
314 /* Optimization: skip to the message header. */
315 if ((flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV) == 0) {
316 if (vstream_fseek(fp, data_offset, SEEK_SET) < 0)
317 msg_fatal("seek error: %m");
318 /* Update the state machine. */
319 state = PC_STATE_HEADER;
320 do_print = (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_HEADER);
321 }
322 }
323 continue;
324 }
325
326 /*
327 * Don't inspect side-effect-free records that aren't printed.
328 */
329 if (do_print == 0)
330 continue;
331 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_OFFSET)
332 vstream_printf("%9lu ", (unsigned long) offset);
333 if (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_RTYPE_DEC)
334 vstream_printf("%3d ", rec_type);
335 switch (rec_type) {
336 case REC_TYPE_TIME:
337 REC_TYPE_TIME_SCAN(STR(buffer), tv);
338 time = tv.tv_sec;
339 vstream_printf("%s: %s", rec_type_name(rec_type),
340 asctime(localtime(&time)));
341 break;
342 case REC_TYPE_WARN:
343 REC_TYPE_WARN_SCAN(STR(buffer), time);
344 vstream_printf("%s: %s", rec_type_name(rec_type),
345 asctime(localtime(&time)));
346 break;
347 case REC_TYPE_CONT: /* REC_TYPE_FILT collision */
348 if (state == PC_STATE_ENV)
349 vstream_printf("%s: ", rec_type_name(rec_type));
350 else if (msg_verbose)
351 vstream_printf("unterminated_text: ");
352 vstream_fwrite(VSTREAM_OUT, STR(buffer), LEN(buffer));
353 if (state == PC_STATE_ENV || msg_verbose
354 || (flags & PC_FLAG_PRINT_OFFSET) != 0) {
355 rec_type = 0;
356 VSTREAM_PUTCHAR('\n');
357 }
358 break;
359 case REC_TYPE_NORM:
360 if (msg_verbose)
361 vstream_printf("%s: ", rec_type_name(rec_type));
362 vstream_fwrite(VSTREAM_OUT, STR(buffer), LEN(buffer));
363 VSTREAM_PUTCHAR('\n');
364 break;
365 case REC_TYPE_DTXT:
366 /* This record type is exposed only with '-v'. */
367 vstream_printf("%s: ", rec_type_name(rec_type));
368 vstream_fwrite(VSTREAM_OUT, STR(buffer), LEN(buffer));
369 VSTREAM_PUTCHAR('\n');
370 break;
371 case REC_TYPE_ATTR:
372 error_text = split_nameval(STR(buffer), &attr_name, &attr_value);
373 if (error_text != 0) {
374 msg_warn("%s: malformed attribute: %s: %.100s",
375 VSTREAM_PATH(fp), error_text, STR(buffer));
376 break;
377 }
378 if (strcmp(attr_name, MAIL_ATTR_CREATE_TIME) == 0) {
379 time = atol(attr_value);
380 vstream_printf("%s: %s", MAIL_ATTR_CREATE_TIME,
381 asctime(localtime(&time)));
382 } else {
383 vstream_printf("%s: %s=%s\n", rec_type_name(rec_type),
384 attr_name, attr_value);
385 }
386 break;
387 default:
388 vstream_printf("%s: %s\n", rec_type_name(rec_type), STR(buffer));
389 break;
390 }
391 prev_type = rec_type;
392
393 /*
394 * In case the next record is broken.
395 */
396 vstream_fflush(VSTREAM_OUT);
397 }
398}
399
400/* usage - explain and terminate */
401
402static NORETURN usage(char *myname)
403{
404 msg_fatal("usage: %s [-b (body text)] [-c config_dir] [-d (decimal record type)] [-e (envelope records)] [-h (header text)] [-q (access queue)] [-v] [file(s)...]",
405 myname);
406}
407
408MAIL_VERSION_STAMP_DECLARE;
409
410int main(int argc, char **argv)
411{
412 VSTRING *buffer;
413 VSTREAM *fp;
414 int ch;
415 int fd;
416 struct stat st;
417 int flags = 0;
418 static char *queue_names[] = {
419 MAIL_QUEUE_MAILDROP,
420 MAIL_QUEUE_INCOMING,
421 MAIL_QUEUE_ACTIVE,
422 MAIL_QUEUE_DEFERRED,
423 MAIL_QUEUE_HOLD,
424 MAIL_QUEUE_SAVED,
425 0,
426 };
427 char **cpp;
428 int tries;
429
430 /*
431 * Fingerprint executables and core dumps.
432 */
433 MAIL_VERSION_STAMP_ALLOCATE;
434
435 /*
436 * To minimize confusion, make sure that the standard file descriptors
437 * are open before opening anything else. XXX Work around for 44BSD where
438 * fstat can return EBADF on an open file descriptor.
439 */
440 for (fd = 0; fd < 3; fd++)
441 if (fstat(fd, &st) == -1
442 && (close(fd), open("/dev/null", O_RDWR, 0)) != fd)
443 msg_fatal("open /dev/null: %m");
444
445 /*
446 * Set up logging.
447 */
448 msg_vstream_init(argv[0], VSTREAM_ERR);
449
450 /*
451 * Parse JCL.
452 */
453 while ((ch = GETOPT(argc, argv, "bc:dehoqv")) > 0) {
454 switch (ch) {
455 case 'b':
456 flags |= PC_FLAG_PRINT_BODY;
457 break;
458 case 'c':
459 if (setenv(CONF_ENV_PATH, optarg, 1) < 0)
460 msg_fatal("out of memory");
461 break;
462 case 'd':
463 flags |= PC_FLAG_PRINT_RTYPE_DEC;
464 break;
465 case 'e':
466 flags |= PC_FLAG_PRINT_ENV;
467 break;
468 case 'h':
469 flags |= PC_FLAG_PRINT_HEADER;
470 break;
471 case 'o':
472 flags |= PC_FLAG_PRINT_OFFSET;
473 break;
474 case 'q':
475 flags |= PC_FLAG_SEARCH_QUEUE;
476 break;
477 case 'v':
478 msg_verbose++;
479 break;
480 default:
481 usage(argv[0]);
482 }
483 }
484 if ((flags & PC_MASK_PRINT_ALL) == 0)
485 flags |= PC_MASK_PRINT_ALL;
486
487 /*
488 * Further initialization...
489 */
490 mail_conf_read();
491
492 /*
493 * Initialize.
494 */
495 buffer = vstring_alloc(10);
496
497 /*
498 * If no file names are given, copy stdin.
499 */
500 if (argc == optind) {
501 vstream_control(VSTREAM_IN,
502 CA_VSTREAM_CTL_PATH("stdin"),
503 CA_VSTREAM_CTL_END);
504 postcat(VSTREAM_IN, buffer, flags);
505 }
506
507 /*
508 * Copy the named queue files in the specified order.
509 */
510 else if (flags & PC_FLAG_SEARCH_QUEUE) {
511 if (chdir(var_queue_dir))
512 msg_fatal("chdir %s: %m", var_queue_dir);
513 while (optind < argc) {
514 if (!mail_queue_id_ok(argv[optind]))
515 msg_fatal("bad mail queue ID: %s", argv[optind]);
516 for (fp = 0, tries = 0; fp == 0 && tries < 2; tries++)
517 for (cpp = queue_names; fp == 0 && *cpp != 0; cpp++)
518 fp = mail_queue_open(*cpp, argv[optind], O_RDONLY, 0);
519 if (fp == 0)
520 msg_fatal("open queue file %s: %m", argv[optind]);
521 postcat(fp, buffer, flags);
522 if (vstream_fclose(fp))
523 msg_warn("close %s: %m", argv[optind]);
524 optind++;
525 }
526 }
527
528 /*
529 * Copy the named files in the specified order.
530 */
531 else {
532 while (optind < argc) {
533 if ((fp = vstream_fopen(argv[optind], O_RDONLY, 0)) == 0)
534 msg_fatal("open %s: %m", argv[optind]);
535 postcat(fp, buffer, flags);
536 if (vstream_fclose(fp))
537 msg_warn("close %s: %m", argv[optind]);
538 optind++;
539 }
540 }
541
542 /*
543 * Clean up.
544 */
545 vstring_free(buffer);
546 exit(0);
547}
